{"lemma":"عِشْقِ","slug":"عِشْقِ","root":"ع.ش.ق","root_slug":"ع-ش-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ش-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n29221","n29224","n29225","n29226"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%90%D8%B4%D9%92%D9%82%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of عَشِقَ (ʕašiqa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"liking with desire (lust), being in love; romantic love (particularly when very strong)","examples":[{"text":"عِشْقِي لَكِ كَالْوَرْدِ فِي حَدِيقَةِ قَلْبِي، يَنْمُو بِجَمَالٍ وَرَائِحَةٍ تَمْلَأ كُلِّ الزَّوَايَا.","english":"My love for you is like a rose in the garden of my heart, it grows with beauty and a fragrance that fills every corner."},{"text":"لِعَيْنَيْكِ مَا يَلْقَى ٱلْفُؤَادُ وَمَا لَقِي / وَلِلْحُبِّ مَا لَمْ يَبْقَ مِنِّي وَمَا بَقِي / وَمَا كُنْتُ مِِمَّنْ يَدْخُلُ ٱلْعِشْقُ قَلْبَهُ / وَلَٰكِنَّ مَنْ يُبْصِرْ جُفُونَكِ يَعْشَقِ"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"passion"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fall in love; to love excessively; to adore","examples":[{"text":"لِعَيْنَيْكِ مَا يَلْقَى ٱلْفُؤَادُ وَمَا لَقِي / وَلِلْحُبِّ مَا لَمْ يَبْقَ مِنِّي وَمَا بَقِي / وَمَا كُنْتُ مِِمَّنْ يَدْخُلُ ٱلْعِشْقُ قَلْبَهُ / وَلَٰكِنَّ مَنْ يُبْصِرْ جُفُونَكِ يَعْشَقِ"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to join"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to connect"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʕiʃq/","/ʕa.ʃi.qa/","/ʕaʃ.ʃa.qa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29221","headword_ar":"عَشِقَ","root":"E$q","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K, [accord. to the TA, said in the Msb to be like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Daraba","text_ar":"ضَرَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but in my copy of the Msb it is correctly said to be of the class of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEiba","text_ar":"تَعِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$oqN","text_ar":"عِشْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$aqN","text_ar":"عَشَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) the latter mentioned by Fr, and said by Ibn-EsSarráj to be thus by poetic license, and with two fet-hahs because two kesrehs are rare in nouns, (S, O,) or the former is a simple subst., and the latter is the inf. n., (Msb,) [and app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEo$aqN","text_ar":"مَعْشَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He loved"},{"kind":"text","text":"(another, S, O, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excessively;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IF, S, O, Msb, K;) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passionately;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with amorous desire;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, agreeably with explanations of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$oqN","text_ar":"عِشْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"admiringly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with blindness to defects in the object of his love;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a disease of the nature of melancholia;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tE$~q","text_ar":"تعشّق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"as trans. is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$iqa","text_ar":"عَشِقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as such. (TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaA$iqN","text_ar":"عَاشِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$iqato","text_ar":"عَشِقَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a she-camel,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, vehemently desirous of the stallion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$iqa bihi","text_ar":"عَشِقَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, stuck to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Easiqa bh","text_ar":"عَسِقَ به"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n29224","headword_ar":"عِشْقٌ","root":"E$q","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(IF, S, O, Msb, K) [generally held to be an inf. n.] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEo$aqN","text_ar":"مَعْشَقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[likewise app. an inf. n.] (O, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Excessive love;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IF, S, O, Msb, K;) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passionate love;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"amorous desire:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attackment to women:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IF, Msb:) or the lover's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"admiration"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eajab","text_ar":"عَجَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eujobu","text_ar":"عُجْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the CK is a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eajabu","text_ar":"عَجَبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the beloved;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and it may be in chasteness and in immorality; (K;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$oqN","text_ar":"عِشْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be in chasteness and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~N","text_ar":"حُبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be in immorality: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blindness of the sense to the faults,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defects, of the beloved:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a disease of the nature of melancholia"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraDN wasowaAsiY~N","text_ar":"مَرَضٌ وَسْوَاسِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which one procures to himself by making his thought to exercise absolute power over the approval of certain forms:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) Th, being asked respecting"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHub~","text_ar":"الحُبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEi$oq","text_ar":"العِشْق"},{"kind":"text","text":", which of them is the more commendable, said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHub~","text_ar":"الحُبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEi$oq","text_ar":"العِشْق"},{"kind":"text","text":"is excess: (TA:) [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~N","text_ar":"حُبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] Ibn-Seenà, [whom we commonly call Avicenna,] in a treatise on"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEi$oq","text_ar":"العِشْق"},{"kind":"text","text":", [regarding it as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"natural propension,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] says that it is not peculiar to the human species, but pervades all existing things of the celestial and the elemental and the vegetable and the mineral and the animal, and that its meaning is not perceived nor known, and is rendered more obscure by explanation thereof: (MF, TA:) it is said in the A that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEi$oq","text_ar":"العِشْق"},{"kind":"text","text":"is derived from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEa$aqapu","text_ar":"العَشَقَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which means the [plant commonly called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labolaAb","text_ar":"لَبْلَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":", because it twines upon trees, and cleaves to them. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["IF","S","O","Msb","K","TA","MF"]},{"entry_id":"n29225","headword_ar":"عَشَقٌ","root":"E$q","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labolaAb","text_ar":"لَبْلَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species of dolichos,"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dolichos lablab"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Linn.]; one of which is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$aqapN","text_ar":"عَشَقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": IDrd says, the [common] people assert that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$aqap","text_ar":"عَشَقَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labolaAbap","text_ar":"لَبْلَابَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O:) accord. to Zj, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$aqapN","text_ar":"عَشَقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain tree"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plant"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that becomes green, and then becomes slender and yellow:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$aqN","text_ar":"عَشَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is its pl. [or rather the coll. gen. n.]: (K:) and Kr says that with the postclassical authors it is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labolaAt","text_ar":"لَبْلَات"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  Also The ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tree called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araAk","text_ar":"اَرَاك"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["O","TA","K"]},{"entry_id":"n29226","headword_ar":"عُشُقٌ","root":"E$q","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", with two dammehs, A camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that keeps to the female which he covers and which desires none but him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA.)       -A2-  And Men"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who trim,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dress,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"put into a good"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"right state, the sets"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so I render"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guruws","text_ar":"غُرُوس"},{"kind":"text","text":", as pl. accord. to general analogy of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garosN","text_ar":"غَرْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of sweet-smelling plants."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, O, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}